check the angle between gamma1 and gamma2

2020-04-17

Set 1

When using the seting 1 17 covariates combinations:

1 2 3 4 5 6 7
dur_MDE age_MDE Greg_FH fatigue hypersomnia axis2 anger_attack
anxious w0_4165 w0_4167 w0_4163 w0_4162 w0_4169 w0_1844
w0_1916 w0_1915 w0_1920 . . . .

\(~\)

We then calculate the \(\hat \alpha\) and estimate \[Y_i = S(\beta_i + b_i + \Gamma_i (\alpha^\prime X)) + \epsilon_i, \text{ } i = 1,2\] The angle between \(\hat \Gamma_1\) and \(\hat \Gamma_2\) is about:

\(\hat \Gamma_1:\)

## [1] -0.0066  0.0008

\(\hat \Gamma_2:\)

## [1] -0.1114  0.0120
angle = cosine(gamma1, gamma2)
acos(angle) * pi / 180 
##              [,1]
## [1,] 0.0001391297

Therefore, the angle is just \(0.0001391297^{\circ}\), almost 0

The box plot of IPWE
